		<td><b>Famicom Powerglove on US NES with US Sensors possible?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I happened across a Famicom version of the powerglove, but it was the glove only. I managed to track down some sensors which work with a US NES and the gloves connector plugs in just fine. The sensor LEDs show it reading the glove input correctly, however, the NES is not registering any inputs. Are the sensors faulty, or is there some kind of compatibility issue? I would have thought so long as the sensor read the glove inputs right, they should go to the NES correctly..<br /><br />I have searched for this and have not been able to come up with an answer.

		

